---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Contribute $5" accent="#4CAF50">
  <div class="content" style="text-align: center;">
    <h1>$5. That's It.</h1>

    <p style="font-size: 1.25rem; max-width: 600px; margin: 1.5rem auto;">
      Arizona Clean Elections lets candidates run without corporate money. All it takes is 220 people contributing $5 each.
    </p>

    <div class="stat-grid" style="max-width: 500px; margin: 2rem auto;">
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-number" style="color: #4CAF50;">$5</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Qualifying contribution</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat">
        <div class="stat-number" style="color: #4CAF50;">220</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Neighbors needed</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div style="background: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid #333; border-radius: 8px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem auto; max-width: 500px;">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">How It Works</h2>
      <p>
        Arizona's Clean Elections system was designed to get corporate money out of politics. When 220 LD-19 residents each contribute $5, the state provides public campaign financing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Your $5 isn't funding attack ads. It's proving that a working-class candidate has community support.
      </p>
      <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-top: 1.5rem;">
        You must be a registered voter in Arizona Legislative District 19 to make a qualifying contribution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="margin: 3rem 0;">
      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600;">Contribution form coming soon.</p>
      <p style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        In the meantime, reach out directly:<br />
        <strong>ramirezforhouse@gmail.com</strong>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div style="text-align: left; max-width: 600px; margin: 3rem auto;">
      <h2>Why $5?</h2>
      <p>
        Most campaigns start with $1,000 dinners and corporate PACs. We start with five-dollar bills from neighbors.
      </p>
      <p>
        Clean Elections means I'm accountable to you, not to donors. If I'm in office and I'm not fighting for the six bills I campaigned on, you know I wasn't bought off &mdash; I just failed. And you can vote me out.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's the deal. $5 to get in the conversation. And a promise to fight like hell once we're there.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
